segue_dave.line: Pale Saints broke up in 1996, while Black Sabbath's "I" was released by I.R.S. Records, a record label which dissolved in the same year...
segue_dave.explanation: Pale Saints was formed as a band in 1996 and Black Sabbath's "Dehumanizer" was released by I.R.S. Records, a record label that stop existing in the same year.
